&ldquo;Fluctuat Nec Mergitur&rdquo; &ldquo;Battu par les flots, mais ne sombre pas. Tossed by the sea, but not sunk.&rdquo;
The centuries-old motto, which appears on the French capital&rsquo;s crest, has been a central rallying cry in the wake of the Paris attacks.
